"""engine_pin — single-source ENGINE_MD5 pin.

One constant, one home. The five prose-only suites import this value instead
of each carrying a duplicate hard-coded literal. When the engine legitimately
changes, re-aim this one line and the entire tooling suite re-anchors.

The pin is a hard-coded literal — never computed at runtime. A pin that
recomputes its own value from the file it is supposed to guard is vacuous:
it can never detect drift. The literal was recorded at the commit that first
introduced it and is updated only by a deliberate, human-approved task.
"""

ENGINE_MD5 = "fadd8f7242d3eb07070f779281d3cb7b"  # re-aimed @ scope-gate-enforce (the verify gate enforces the declared §5 Scope, build-scope-lock task 2/3: NEW _declared_scope parses the frozen scope-decl-template grammar — backticked tokens · FIRST 'Scope (may touch):' line · ./… task dir · '/' project root · bare sibling-of-previous · outside-root dropped fail-closed · directory token = WHOLE subtree · no line = None UNDECLARED (grandfathered, never retro-red) · garbage line = [] empty allowlist, no cover. At the tests->build advance a declared task freezes the project tree git-free: _scope_walk {rel: md5} pruning the ONE named exclusion constant (_SCOPE_EXCLUDE_DIRS .git/.add/__pycache__/node_modules + .DS_Store/*.pyc) into sidecar .add/tasks/<slug>/scope-snapshot.json, anchored in state.json by the sidecar-bytes md5 — UNCONDITIONAL overwrite like the tripwire. At a COMPLETING gate _scope_guard (after _tamper_guard, BEFORE the waiver write — never launderable; HARD-STOP never calls it) re-walks and refuses scope_violation '<p1> · … (N total)' when touched (modified∪added∪deleted, unreadable-now = touched) falls outside every declared token, or scope_snapshot_tampered when the sidecar is missing/diverged/unparseable against its anchor, or scope_anchor_missing (v2 re-freeze, refute-driven) when the anchor was erased while the sidecar survives — anchor and sidecar co-witness each other, so either single-file erase is caught and only the accepted two-file floor remains; v3 re-freeze (close-gap-before-gate): an UNDECLARED tests->build crossing CLEANS UP a previous declaration's leftovers — pops the stale anchor, unlinks the stale sidecar — so a declared->undeclared re-cross is never falsely refused (UNDECLARED is never refused, on every path). check gains the standing monitor: pending violation or tampered baseline = WARN, never red. Heal routing of a violation is scope-violation-heal (NEXT task). Carries the prior engine-merge-base-enforcement wave-ledger gate (cmd_